properties.description: Imagineering My Way posted a photo: LA Regional 4th of July Parade The city of Ontario California takes pride in its Independence Day Parade. Since 2006 they have been proud of the telecast Magnolia Street Productions has provided of the parade both live and in repeat performances on television stations and cable systems throughout California. In 2011 Magnolia Street Productions coverage of the event includes, for the first time, live streaming of the parade over the internet. Anyone can see the parade live, as it happens, from literally anywhere on the planet with an internet connection. properties.title: 1923 - Mounted Troop Cavalry, Fort Riley, Kansas
properties.description: clotho98 posted a photo: Postcard dated October 23, 1923, to Lena Citareola. The description on the card reads: Mounted Troop Cavalry, Fort Riley, Kansas. -- Fort Riley is located in the northeast section of Kansas. It is one of the oldest and largest posts in the United States. It was established May 5, 1855. There are about 500 troops stationed at the post. in the post is located an artillery school. It is considered the best post in the country for artillery practice, being crossed by a river and hilly.

properties.description: skarpi posted a photo: Icelandic sheep in front of Mountain Hekla (1.488 m) one of the most active stratovolcanoes in the southern part of Iceland. properties.title: Mennonite Farmer Plowing with Horses - Grabill, Indiana
properties.description: Alton S. posted a photo: Grabill is in Allen County, not too far out of Fort Wayne near the Ohio border. 420 households, many of them - if not most of them - belong to "Old Order" Amish and Mennonite families. A very special place - many of my own ancestors were Mennonites who joined the German Baptist Brethren after a generation or so in America. Most of the Brethren in Indiana seem to be centered in Nappanee. My father worked here in perhaps the 1970s at a steering wheel factory staffed largely with Amish who were holding their first jobs away from the farm.

properties.title: Mozada saltea
properties.description: Eduardo Amorim posted a photo: "Le hablo de un Nueve de Julio, de cuando la Independencia... Mire que apuntaba fiero la Patria nuevita y tierna... La toreaban por el Norte tan duro que era una pena... Tropas del Alto Per, del Rey o tal vez la Reina, toda gente veterana muy bien armada y dispuesta... Menos mal que Martn Gemes con su mozada saltea y sus bravos infernales les han cerrado las puertas..." Fragmento de "Le hablo de un Nueve de Julio", de Len Benars San Antonio de Areco, Provincia de Buenos Aires, Argentina Amigos, visitem: www.visiteareco.comA mis hermanos Argentinos en su Nueve de Julio

properties.title: Bring on the Dancing Horses
properties.description: s0ulsurfing posted a photo: Four photos uploaded today from the NatWest Island Games opening ceremony and parade. I really enjoyed just being there, lots of colour and energy and 40,000 people on the streets of Ryde to see it apparently. These horse costumes were really spectacular and i tried to capture some of the chaotic fun by getting up close with the 10mm wide angle lensMore shots from the opening and closing ceremonies as well as photo galleries from all seven days of the games can be viewed at my website. I did take some new William photos in the last few days, hoping to have time to look at them and upload a few by early next week. ----------------------------------- 2011 Jason Swain, All Rights Reserved This image is not available for use on websites, blogs or other media without the explicit written permission of the photographer. ----------------------------------- Links to my website, facebook and twitter can be found on my flickr profile -----------------------------------

properties.title: Schwalbenschwanz  BUTTERFLY I
properties.description: Anne STA posted a photo: Der Schwalbenschwanz ist neben dem Segelfalter einer der grten und aufflligsten Tagfalter des deutschsprachigen Raums und hat eine Flgelspannweite von 50 bis 75 Millimetern. Er ist gelb und schwarz gemustert mit einer blauen Binde und roten Augenflecken an der hinteren Innenseite der Hinterflgel. An den Hinterflgeln stehen kurze, grtenteils schwarz gefrbte Schwnzchen ab. Er hat lange Haare an den Vorderbeinen, die als Putzkmmchen dienen.[1] Die zweite Generation unterscheidet sich durch krftige Farben und gelb bestubte schwarze Zeichnungselemente von der ersten Generation. Die Raupen werden ca. 45 Millimeter lang und sind unbehaart. Sie sind grn gefrbt und haben schwarze Querstreifen mit gelben oder orangeroten Punkten. Selten tritt eine weie Form der Raupe auf, die statt der grnen eine weie Grundfarbe hat.[1]
